      "id": "bug-011",
      "timestamp": "2026-04-15T19:28:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "internal/sandbox/staging.go:83:41: undefined: syscall.Stat_t",
      "file": "cli/internal/sandbox/staging.go",
      "root_cause": "CleanStale used syscall.Stat_t and os.Getuid inline. syscall.Stat_t is not defined on Windows, so cross-compilation for GOOS=windows fails at the build step. Local `go build` on Linux compiled fine and hid the problem; the release workflow cross-compiles for six targets and caught it.",
      "fix": "Extracted the ownership check into a platform-specific helper isOwnedByCurrentUser(info). Added cli/internal/sandbox/ownership_unix.go (build tag !windows) with the real syscall.Stat_t/os.Getuid check, and cli/internal/sandbox/ownership_windows.go (build tag windows) that returns true (Windows uses per-user temp paths by default). Removed syscall import from staging.go.",
      "tags": [
        "cross-platform",
        "windows",
        "sandbox",
        "build-tags",
        "syscall",
        "release-blocker"
      ],
